WEBVTT

00:23.565 --> 00:25.442
Do you not realize
what kind of danger we're in?

00:27.819 --> 00:30.571
- Shit happens.
- What is wrong with you two?

00:30.572 --> 00:31.698
Why are you acting like…

00:34.200 --> 00:36.201
Nami, let me see your leg.

00:36.202 --> 00:38.746
Oh, the cook's gonna be sorry
he missed this.

00:38.747 --> 00:42.041
No, I mean that paint, Nami.

00:42.042 --> 00:43.501
You have to get it off.

00:44.794 --> 00:46.212
I'm good.

00:59.309 --> 01:00.769
Do you remember where you are?

01:01.811 --> 01:07.399
I remember everything, but it's like
I couldn't control how I felt.

01:07.400 --> 01:09.818
That symbol is the marking
of a very dangerous agent

01:09.819 --> 01:10.903
called Miss Goldenweek.

01:10.904 --> 01:13.655
She uses this special hypnotic paint

01:13.656 --> 01:16.825
that alters the victim's emotional state
when absorbed into the skin,

01:16.826 --> 01:19.119
literally coloring how you feel.

01:19.120 --> 01:21.663
Breaking that mark
is the only way to break her control.

01:21.664 --> 01:25.084
That's some crazy stuff
you had to go through, Nami.

01:25.085 --> 01:28.505
I would never
let something like that control me.

01:31.508 --> 01:34.719
Hey, laughing guy,
you literally have paint on your leg.

01:36.179 --> 01:38.889
- No, I don't.
- Yes, you do.

01:38.890 --> 01:40.224
Hey, hey, hey!

01:40.225 --> 01:42.684
I'm ticklish.

01:42.685 --> 01:45.647
Guys, stop messing around.
Baroque Works is right outside.

01:48.608 --> 01:52.319
Listen, I keep a lockpick in my boot.
If one of us can--

01:52.320 --> 01:54.196
These shackles are made of wax.

01:54.197 --> 01:56.116
There's no lock to pick.

01:57.784 --> 02:00.954
We're gonna just have to hope
that one of your crew is looking for us.

02:01.996 --> 02:03.873
Oh no. Usopp.

02:04.541 --> 02:07.252
The last time I saw him,
he was falling in a rockslide. I…

02:08.128 --> 02:09.336
I hope he's okay.

02:09.337 --> 02:11.004
What about Sanji?

02:11.005 --> 02:12.714
That guy?

02:12.715 --> 02:15.426
He is definitely lost in the jungle.

02:19.764 --> 02:21.598
- Then we're on our own.
- No, we're not.

02:21.599 --> 02:24.519
Luffy is still out there.
He'll come for us.

02:25.019 --> 02:26.645
Miss Goldenweek got to him too.

02:26.646 --> 02:29.565
Wherever he is,
he is not the Luffy you know right now.

02:29.566 --> 02:31.067
Don't bet against Luffy.

02:31.734 --> 02:32.819
Besides,

02:33.653 --> 02:34.695
we're not dead yet.

02:34.696 --> 02:37.532
That is what I am worried about.

02:38.449 --> 02:40.702
This house, these shackles.

02:41.578 --> 02:43.787
They're the work
of Miss Goldenweek's partner, Mr. 3.

02:43.788 --> 02:45.582
Whatever he's planning,

02:46.416 --> 02:48.168
you're gonna wish you were dead.

03:12.192 --> 03:14.569
No need to keep your compliments
to yourself.

03:15.111 --> 03:17.030
What do you think of my latest piece?

03:18.031 --> 03:19.324
I love that he's screaming.

03:20.158 --> 03:21.492
Of course you do.

03:22.368 --> 03:23.994
Did our captives give you trouble?

03:23.995 --> 03:27.372
The swordsman and navigator never
saw me coming. The princess ran off.

03:27.373 --> 03:28.707
She didn't get far.

03:28.708 --> 03:30.417
There's one more name on the list.

03:30.418 --> 03:31.669
The captain.

03:32.420 --> 03:35.214
- Where is he?
- At the beach, having a picnic.

03:35.215 --> 03:37.090
You were supposed to bring him to me.

03:37.091 --> 03:38.259
Well, I want to keep him.

03:38.760 --> 03:39.677
Now, now.

03:40.428 --> 03:43.347
- We've discussed this.
- Well, I need a new toy.

03:43.348 --> 03:46.183
Then you shouldn't have broken
all of your old ones.

03:46.184 --> 03:48.227
Fine. Maybe you can play with me.

03:48.228 --> 03:50.271
Oh!

03:51.397 --> 03:53.900
On second thought,
how can I say no to that face?

03:54.567 --> 03:58.112
Have your fun. When you're done with him,
bring him back.

03:59.155 --> 04:02.659
I need him to complete my masterwork.

04:04.827 --> 04:08.039
Looks like a birthday cake.
Is it my birthday?

04:08.539 --> 04:11.125
No, pet, but it does have candles.

04:11.709 --> 04:14.127
Now that those giants
have been neutralized,

04:14.128 --> 04:16.464
there's no one else to spoil our party.

04:19.300 --> 04:20.260
Hmm.

04:32.063 --> 04:34.440
Luffy! Luffy!

04:35.233 --> 04:36.942
Luffy!

04:36.943 --> 04:38.361
Man, am I glad to see you.

04:40.321 --> 04:44.908
We got a problem. It's Baroque Works.
They got Vivi and Nami and Zoro.

04:44.909 --> 04:47.619
They're building some crazy torture device
in the middle of a meadow.

04:47.620 --> 04:50.164
It's seriously freaky, man.

04:50.665 --> 04:54.710
I figured if we go get them,
you do your Gum Gum thing and, bam,

04:54.711 --> 04:56.379
we can get the hell off this island.

04:57.088 --> 04:58.630
It's all my fault.

04:58.631 --> 05:02.385
No, it is absolutely the fault
of those insane assassins.

05:03.052 --> 05:04.887
The lady on the ship warned me.

05:06.306 --> 05:08.558
She said if I didn't take
her offer to hide,

05:09.517 --> 05:12.228
Baroque Works would hurt my friends.

05:12.854 --> 05:14.897
And it's all because of me.

05:19.652 --> 05:21.237
Luffy, what's on your face?

05:21.738 --> 05:22.904
All going to die.

05:22.905 --> 05:25.949
Hey. Hey, this isn't you, okay?

05:25.950 --> 05:27.534
Listen. We got this.

05:27.535 --> 05:28.744
You and me.

05:28.745 --> 05:30.620
Captains Usopp and Luffy.

05:30.621 --> 05:33.123
Just like Yasopp and Shanks.

05:33.124 --> 05:37.628
Following our dreams and fighting
against anyone that stands in our way.

05:38.629 --> 05:40.506
And I can't do this by myself, so

05:41.466 --> 05:44.260
whatever's going on,
you gotta snap out of it. Please.

05:45.595 --> 05:46.429
Come on, Luffy.

05:47.096 --> 05:48.931
We need you. Come on!

05:53.269 --> 05:57.022
Hey, I know things look bad,
but you don't give up.

05:57.023 --> 05:58.440
You never give up.

05:58.441 --> 06:00.192
<i>Fa-la-la-la</i>

06:00.193 --> 06:01.193
I'll be back.

06:01.194 --> 06:03.445
<i>La-la-la-la-la-la</i>

06:03.446 --> 06:06.573
- <i>La-la-la-la-la-la</i>
- I'm sorry, Usopp.

06:06.574 --> 06:09.076
<i>Fa-la-la-la-la-la-la</i>

06:09.077 --> 06:11.536
<i>La-la, la-la</i>

06:11.537 --> 06:13.539
<i>La-la-la</i>

06:15.249 --> 06:17.460
I'm throwing a picnic for my new dolly.

06:20.088 --> 06:21.172
You.

06:31.224 --> 06:35.686
Okay, Usopp. Think.
There are four assassins on this island.

06:36.896 --> 06:40.233
First plan.
You hide until they all go away.

06:41.651 --> 06:42.860
But then your friends die.

06:43.861 --> 06:46.197
Second plan. You fight them.

06:48.324 --> 06:49.575
And then you die.

06:50.743 --> 06:51.701
Painfully.

06:51.702 --> 06:52.745
Third plan.

06:54.705 --> 06:55.832
You find…

06:57.500 --> 06:59.043
someone else

07:00.002 --> 07:01.295
to fight them.

07:02.839 --> 07:03.923
Sanji.

07:07.885 --> 07:08.970
Sanji!

07:11.347 --> 07:12.932
Nami?

07:13.850 --> 07:14.976
Vivi?

07:16.102 --> 07:17.562
Luffy?

07:19.063 --> 07:20.189
Usopp!

07:22.608 --> 07:23.860
Mosshead.

07:28.364 --> 07:30.908
Well, that's something
you don't see every day.

08:13.451 --> 08:15.535
You were right.

08:15.536 --> 08:17.455
This is worse than death.

08:19.624 --> 08:21.917
I trust the three of you
are uncomfortable.

08:21.918 --> 08:23.293
So you're Mr. 3.

08:23.294 --> 08:24.294
What gave it away?

08:24.295 --> 08:27.840
Probably the "3" in your… …hair.

08:30.134 --> 08:32.761
We were pretty pissed we didn't get
to kill you all at Whisky Peak.

08:32.762 --> 08:35.223
But we'll make up for it
by killing you now. Hmm.

08:36.224 --> 08:39.810
You know the problem with
some of my associates in Baroque Works?

08:40.811 --> 08:42.939
They're so focused on the work

08:43.523 --> 08:46.359
they forget to be… baroque.

08:47.610 --> 08:48.735
Take these two,

08:48.736 --> 08:51.947
gifted with such glorious
devil fruit abilities.

08:51.948 --> 08:53.699
Yet how do they choose to use them?

08:54.200 --> 08:56.952
As killers for hire.

08:56.953 --> 08:58.036
Brutes.

08:58.037 --> 09:00.665
Their deeds will be forgotten by history.

09:01.749 --> 09:03.209
Not mine.

09:03.709 --> 09:05.460
Is this speech the torture?

09:05.461 --> 09:07.505
Nami!

09:08.172 --> 09:10.216
Would you do the honors?

09:12.510 --> 09:13.761
So gross.

09:21.769 --> 09:23.271
Voilà.

09:29.026 --> 09:30.318
Oh!

09:30.319 --> 09:32.571
It's raining wax.

09:32.572 --> 09:38.368
The wax mist sprinkling down
on your heads will cover you and harden,

09:38.369 --> 09:41.831
turning your bodies
into beautiful wax sculptures.

09:42.832 --> 09:46.376
You should be honored.
You're dying for art.

09:46.377 --> 09:47.461
Oh my God.

09:47.962 --> 09:49.588
That's your genius plan?

09:49.589 --> 09:50.631
Hmm?

09:51.132 --> 09:52.966
Wait around for some damn wax to fall?

09:52.967 --> 09:56.303
I wouldn't expect
dullards like you to understand.

09:56.304 --> 09:59.723
We're assassins.
Let's assassinate them and go home.

09:59.724 --> 10:03.018
I understand we're assassins,
but I am an artist.

10:03.019 --> 10:05.312
I could blow them up.
You are wasting our time.

10:05.313 --> 10:06.438
Vivi.

10:06.439 --> 10:08.357
- Need I remind you…
- Look at Zoro.

10:09.859 --> 10:13.612
- He still has his swords.
- My wax will freeze their expressions.

10:13.613 --> 10:16.031
Immortalize their suffering.

10:16.032 --> 10:18.783
The pain. The despair.

10:18.784 --> 10:20.911
The slow death…

10:22.580 --> 10:24.664
…is the entire point.

10:24.665 --> 10:26.125
That's bullshit.

10:27.460 --> 10:28.835
You call yourself an artist?

10:28.836 --> 10:31.630
I've stolen from the finest museums
in all of the East Blue,

10:31.631 --> 10:34.133
and your art talk is all crap.

10:35.885 --> 10:37.093
Does my work offend you?

10:37.094 --> 10:39.387
Your work is a lie.

10:39.388 --> 10:40.680
Look at Zoro.

10:40.681 --> 10:43.684
He's not suffering. He's giggling.

10:45.102 --> 10:46.187
Girl's got a point.

11:05.122 --> 11:07.040
Shouldn't have let me keep my swords.

11:07.041 --> 11:11.711
I wouldn't dream of immortalizing
Roronoa Zoro without them.

11:11.712 --> 11:14.381
Then there's nothing stopping me
from cutting myself free,

11:14.382 --> 11:17.300
and leaving this island with your head.

11:17.301 --> 11:18.552
There he is.

11:20.596 --> 11:22.014
Mmm.

11:25.226 --> 11:26.227
What the hell?

11:26.727 --> 11:29.772
My wax is hard as steel.

11:30.773 --> 11:34.735
Clearly, you're not strong enough
to cut it, but do keep trying.

11:35.361 --> 11:36.278
It's highly amusing.

11:40.658 --> 11:41.951
There it is.

11:42.993 --> 11:46.706
That's the reaction I've been looking for.

11:48.207 --> 11:49.250
Mmm.

11:56.340 --> 12:00.343
Nobody ever wanted to play with me
until I got my special paint.

12:00.344 --> 12:02.470
Now people do whatever I want.

12:02.471 --> 12:06.266
Green will make you so calm
you'd accept your own death.

12:06.267 --> 12:09.978
Yellow will make you laugh
through even the most painful torture.

12:09.979 --> 12:11.188
And blue?

12:12.398 --> 12:18.028
Blue will make you sadder than you've
ever felt in your whole entire life.

12:18.529 --> 12:20.406
But you already know that.

12:21.699 --> 12:22.700
Tea?

12:24.910 --> 12:26.662
My friends

12:27.163 --> 12:28.580
are going to die.

12:28.581 --> 12:31.916
You're better off without them.
Friends let you down.

12:31.917 --> 12:33.084
Not like toys.

12:33.085 --> 12:36.296
When toys stop being fun,
you can put them back in the box.

12:36.297 --> 12:39.591
I tried to explain that to my parents,
but they didn't understand.

12:39.592 --> 12:42.344
So I painted them too
and put them in a box.

12:44.221 --> 12:46.182
They were so noisy in there.

12:46.807 --> 12:48.392
For the first few days.

12:55.441 --> 12:56.525
You're crying.

12:57.026 --> 12:58.360
It's getting boring.

13:07.787 --> 13:08.995
There you go.

13:08.996 --> 13:11.957
Now you can relax
and forget all about those silly friends.

13:17.421 --> 13:18.714
How do you like the tea?

13:22.259 --> 13:25.888
I said, how does dolly like the tea?

13:26.722 --> 13:31.435
I'm going to save my

13:32.144 --> 13:34.354
friends.

13:34.355 --> 13:37.441
How do you like the tea?

13:54.667 --> 13:59.255
This tea is delicious.

14:01.882 --> 14:03.092
Good dolly.

14:13.853 --> 14:17.480
Chains, red wine,
a whole load of candle wax.

14:17.481 --> 14:19.775
Somebody had a good time here.

14:33.831 --> 14:34.998
Hmm.

14:34.999 --> 14:36.792
What do we have here?

14:54.852 --> 14:56.770
Hmm. Where's my folder?

15:01.734 --> 15:05.820
Well, you guys
all got yourselves in trouble again,

15:05.821 --> 15:07.364
and I guess

15:08.157 --> 15:10.826
it's up to old Sanji to save the day.

15:48.948 --> 15:51.992
This is the shitty restaurant.
May I take your reservation?

15:55.371 --> 15:57.373
<i>Careful, Mr. 3.</i>

15:57.873 --> 16:00.417
<i>Is that how you speak to your superior?</i>

16:01.168 --> 16:03.337
Oh, my apologies,

16:04.421 --> 16:05.422
Mr. 0.

16:06.507 --> 16:08.967
The Marines have become aware
of our movements.

16:08.968 --> 16:11.344
Even with our voices altered,

16:11.345 --> 16:15.348
the use of transponder snails
will soon be too much of a risk.

16:15.349 --> 16:18.978
<i>I trust I only need to ask this once.</i>

16:19.853 --> 16:22.940
Are the princess and the Straw Hats dead?

16:23.607 --> 16:27.277
Oh, yes. Lying in a pool
of their own blood as we speak, sir.

16:27.861 --> 16:29.697
<i>I'm surprised, Mr. 3.</i>

16:30.739 --> 16:32.991
<i>You usually insist on taking your time.</i>

16:32.992 --> 16:35.827
<i>Yeah, well,
I was gonna torture them for longer,</i>

16:35.828 --> 16:38.496
<i>but that green-haired one
just really got on my nerves.</i>

16:38.497 --> 16:39.455
<i>He's so annoying.</i>

16:39.456 --> 16:41.625
<i>I couldn't shut him up fast enough,
to be honest.</i>

16:54.638 --> 16:56.306
As long as it's done.

16:57.766 --> 17:02.562
<i>I've dispatched the Unluckies to verify
and to clean up the mess.</i>

17:02.563 --> 17:04.355
<i>They should be arriving as we speak.</i>

17:04.356 --> 17:06.358
I look forward to welcoming them, sir.

17:07.443 --> 17:11.362
<i>Oh, and I should warn you,
Miss Friday hasn't eaten in a while.</i>

17:11.363 --> 17:15.701
Not since that unfortunate incident
at the orphanage.

17:32.051 --> 17:34.053
You've gotta be fucking joking.

17:55.824 --> 17:58.118
Sanji. They got you too.

18:00.120 --> 18:01.663
Help!

18:02.331 --> 18:04.500
Somebody help me!

18:05.167 --> 18:06.418
Please!

18:16.053 --> 18:16.970
Brogy?

18:18.055 --> 18:19.223
Brogy!

18:35.239 --> 18:38.241
Brave warrior Usopp.

18:38.242 --> 18:40.118
Brogy, you're alive!

18:40.119 --> 18:45.123
It seems Dorry's sword wasn't sharp enough
to grant me a swift end.

18:45.124 --> 18:47.834
But if I am to meet my gods today,

18:47.835 --> 18:52.630
I am glad the last sight I see
is the face of a friend.

18:52.631 --> 18:55.133
Whoa, whoa, nobody's meeting any gods.

18:55.134 --> 18:57.051
Your duel wasn't a fair fight.

18:57.052 --> 18:58.679
Someone poisoned your ale.

18:59.179 --> 19:00.721
They wanted to sabotage you.

19:00.722 --> 19:03.641
What villain would do such a thing?

19:03.642 --> 19:06.061
The same people that kidnapped my friends.

19:06.687 --> 19:09.188
They're in trouble right now.
They need help.

19:09.189 --> 19:11.399
Say no more.

19:11.400 --> 19:14.153
We will defeat our foes together,

19:14.736 --> 19:16.445
the Elbaph way,

19:16.446 --> 19:18.031
with honor

19:18.949 --> 19:20.741
and steel.

19:20.742 --> 19:21.785
Aah!

19:30.127 --> 19:31.753
You don't look so good.

19:34.673 --> 19:37.801
Perhaps my offer was a bit hasty.

19:38.594 --> 19:40.845
But no matter the danger,

19:40.846 --> 19:44.223
I'm sure Captain Usopp can handle it,

19:44.224 --> 19:46.685
just like in your stories, eh?

19:47.436 --> 19:52.024
What chance do those fiends stand
against the Lord of Destruction?

19:53.859 --> 19:55.027
About that…

19:57.446 --> 20:00.199
Look, a mole monster's one thing, but

20:01.241 --> 20:03.326
these Baroque Works guys are different.

20:03.327 --> 20:05.329
They're crazy powerful with

20:06.330 --> 20:07.705
crazy powers.

20:07.706 --> 20:09.624
I understand.

20:09.625 --> 20:11.125
You are scared.

20:11.126 --> 20:12.586
I'm not scared.

20:14.588 --> 20:16.547
Who said scared? I… I didn't say that.

20:16.548 --> 20:18.091
You are small.

20:18.592 --> 20:20.010
And stringy.

20:20.510 --> 20:23.722
And your friends' lives are at stake.

20:24.223 --> 20:27.100
It makes sense you are scared.

20:28.936 --> 20:32.189
Any true warrior would be.

20:33.357 --> 20:36.860
A warrior's fear is a good thing.

20:37.361 --> 20:39.071
It means you care.

20:39.863 --> 20:41.573
Gives you purpose.

20:42.074 --> 20:47.287
I would never trust my life to a warrior
who claimed never to have been afraid.

20:49.790 --> 20:51.332
You really believe that?

20:51.333 --> 20:53.709
In the cave, you asked me

20:53.710 --> 20:56.880
how can one face death without fear?

20:58.090 --> 21:02.468
True bravery is not the absence of fear,

21:02.469 --> 21:05.930
but going into battle in spite of it.

21:05.931 --> 21:08.015
I'm not a giant like you.

21:08.016 --> 21:10.352
If I go into battle alone,

21:11.895 --> 21:13.020
I'll die.

21:13.021 --> 21:15.606
An honorable death,

21:15.607 --> 21:19.361
trying to save your friends.

21:45.137 --> 21:46.638
Polly want a cracker?

21:53.437 --> 21:55.355
<i>Is there some trouble, Mr. 3?</i>

22:06.491 --> 22:08.952
I'm gonna have to put you on hold.

22:15.751 --> 22:16.752
Aah!

22:24.593 --> 22:25.761
Aah!

23:03.256 --> 23:04.341
Sorry.

23:05.092 --> 23:06.343
Your pets are dead.

23:27.280 --> 23:29.865
And I take it the Straw Hats are not?

23:29.866 --> 23:33.744
Tell me, who am I really speaking to?

23:33.745 --> 23:34.996
<i>You can call me…</i>

23:37.457 --> 23:38.875
Mr. Prince.

23:39.418 --> 23:41.502
<i>Then know this, Mr. Prince.</i>

23:41.503 --> 23:47.258
<i>The Straw Hat Pirates will regret
ever taking Princess Vivi on board.</i>

23:47.259 --> 23:48.342
<i>And you</i>

23:48.343 --> 23:51.012
will regret taking this call.

24:20.625 --> 24:22.043
Hello, gorgeous.

24:29.926 --> 24:32.344
- It's getting hard to move.
- And breathe.

24:32.345 --> 24:33.846
I can't cut through this wax,

24:33.847 --> 24:35.556
but I can cut through my legs.

24:35.557 --> 24:38.100
You're going to cut off your feet?
What kind of a plan is that?

24:38.101 --> 24:39.644
Better than being dead.

24:40.270 --> 24:41.312
He's really doing it.

24:41.313 --> 24:43.814
How do you expect to fight them
without your legs?

24:43.815 --> 24:45.358
If you're scared to watch, look away!

24:45.901 --> 24:48.195
This is disgusting! Stop it!

24:51.448 --> 24:54.450
At least free the others.
I'm the one Baroque Works really wants.

24:54.451 --> 24:57.953
The moment they helped you,
they made our list.

24:57.954 --> 25:01.708
You cannot save them,
and you're too late to save Alabasta.

25:02.334 --> 25:03.919
He's trying to get under your skin.

25:05.086 --> 25:08.547
How much do you know
about your new friend's homeland?

25:08.548 --> 25:11.843
The people there
blame their troubles on the king.

25:12.844 --> 25:15.972
- Her father.
- My father wants to save my country.

25:16.473 --> 25:18.766
Baroque Works are the ones destroying it.

25:18.767 --> 25:21.268
Whatever the cause,
a rebellion is brewing.

25:21.269 --> 25:24.480
It's small, easily contained, until now.

25:24.481 --> 25:26.483
You kept up with the news lately?

25:29.778 --> 25:31.695
"The tides are turning in Alabasta

25:31.696 --> 25:36.450
as thousands of royal soldiers
switch sides to join the rebellion."

25:36.451 --> 25:39.620
Thousands? Gee, that sounds like a lot.

25:39.621 --> 25:41.872
- Wonder what changed their mind.
- Or who.

25:41.873 --> 25:43.958
Why are you doing this?

25:43.959 --> 25:46.794
What does Baroque Works
want from Alabasta?

25:46.795 --> 25:49.881
That's Mr. 0's secret. Sh.

25:53.093 --> 25:54.718
But you got to love the irony.

25:54.719 --> 25:56.804
Alabasta's about to have a civil war,

25:56.805 --> 25:58.806
and the one person who could stop it

25:58.807 --> 26:01.183
is about to die way out here.

26:01.184 --> 26:02.561
Useless.

26:03.311 --> 26:04.646
And alone.

26:08.900 --> 26:11.570
That freak wants us to die scared.

26:12.195 --> 26:13.947
I'm not gonna give him that satisfaction.

26:20.036 --> 26:22.454
Don't worry. Luffy will come.

26:22.455 --> 26:24.999
You lot don't give up, do you?

26:25.000 --> 26:26.334
Are you gonna give up?

26:27.419 --> 26:28.503
On your kingdom?

26:29.379 --> 26:30.505
Don't lose hope.

26:31.381 --> 26:34.384
Trust me. Whatever Miss Goldenweek
is doing to Luffy,

26:35.677 --> 26:37.554
I can guarantee he's fighting it.

26:41.766 --> 26:44.561
Red makes you angry
at any target I choose.

26:45.061 --> 26:46.562
And a naughty dolly like you

26:46.563 --> 26:48.023
deserves to be punished.

26:49.107 --> 26:51.443
Right now, Mr. 3 is killing your friends.

26:51.943 --> 26:53.485
How does that make you feel?

26:53.486 --> 26:56.323
It makes me furious!

27:02.120 --> 27:03.997
You still want to save your friends?

27:08.585 --> 27:11.588
This is my favorite color.

27:12.213 --> 27:16.551
Did you know, on the color spectrum,
black is the absence of light?

27:17.260 --> 27:20.597
On my palette, it's the absence of hope.

27:21.431 --> 27:23.932
That's why I call it Betrayal Black.

27:23.933 --> 27:26.603
It makes you give up
on everything you believe in.

27:28.355 --> 27:31.107
Do you have a dream, dolly?

27:32.150 --> 27:34.735
I'm going to find the One Piece,

27:34.736 --> 27:38.447
and I will be King of the Pirates!

27:38.448 --> 27:39.491
Mm-hmm.

27:53.797 --> 27:55.840
Not anymore.

27:57.884 --> 27:59.426
I've always been lonely.

27:59.427 --> 28:01.221
That's my curse.

28:02.347 --> 28:03.807
But yours is much sadder.

28:04.391 --> 28:06.142
It's the same
as anyone with a devil fruit.

28:07.977 --> 28:08.978
The sea.

28:10.146 --> 28:11.189
One little dip,

28:11.815 --> 28:14.025
and your dreams will never come true.

28:16.778 --> 28:18.446
Walk into the ocean.

28:29.582 --> 28:31.126
That's it.

28:33.211 --> 28:34.212
Don't look back!

28:35.213 --> 28:37.549
Now, repeat after me.

28:38.258 --> 28:40.426
I will never find the One Piece.

28:40.427 --> 28:45.849
I will never find

28:46.349 --> 28:47.726
the One…

28:51.438 --> 28:54.440
I will never be King of the Pirates.

28:54.441 --> 28:55.442
I…

28:56.651 --> 28:57.610
will…

28:59.320 --> 29:00.447
never…

29:01.364 --> 29:02.282
be…

29:03.324 --> 29:04.367
King…

29:04.951 --> 29:06.618
of… the…

29:06.619 --> 29:07.495
Luffy!

29:09.330 --> 29:10.707
Don't say it!

29:14.502 --> 29:15.920
I'm coming for you, buddy!

29:16.504 --> 29:18.130
You ruined my fun!

29:18.131 --> 29:19.923
Now you'll be my new dolly.

29:19.924 --> 29:22.509
You're not coming anywhere near me,
Creepy Longstocking! Whoa!

29:22.510 --> 29:23.428
Ha ha! Whoo!

29:28.141 --> 29:30.477
Luffy! Luffy!

29:32.020 --> 29:32.979
I got you.

29:34.230 --> 29:35.899
Captain Usopp to the rescue!

29:38.359 --> 29:39.569
Come on.

29:58.254 --> 29:59.839
Where's the rest of the crew?

30:16.606 --> 30:18.233
It's almost complete.

30:39.337 --> 30:40.964
Oh, man.

30:41.464 --> 30:43.298
You guys are in for it now.

30:43.299 --> 30:44.425
Who's this joker?

30:46.344 --> 30:47.345
We're the heroes.

30:48.471 --> 30:52.724
I am surprised you managed
to escape my partner's colors trap,

30:52.725 --> 30:55.270
but if you're here to save your friends,

30:56.604 --> 30:57.814
you're too late.

31:12.829 --> 31:14.121
Are they dead?

31:14.122 --> 31:15.247
Not quite.

31:15.248 --> 31:19.084
I estimate they have
a few minutes of air left in their lungs.

31:19.085 --> 31:21.503
But that's more time than you have.

31:21.504 --> 31:23.298
You did this.

31:24.549 --> 31:27.844
You're the one
who ruined the giants' duel too.

31:28.344 --> 31:31.972
That's right. I am the mastermind.

31:31.973 --> 31:33.433
Then you will pay.

31:34.934 --> 31:36.227
Beatdown time, baby.

31:37.270 --> 31:39.814
I'll be right here, buddy.
Go get him, Luffy.

31:46.321 --> 31:47.989
Usopp! Let's split up!

31:48.489 --> 31:50.449
Wait! They're gonna die!

31:50.450 --> 31:51.910
I know you'll never let them!

31:56.539 --> 32:00.334
He's not on our list.
Doesn't mean we can't kill him though.

32:00.335 --> 32:02.921
You hear that? You're gonna die.

32:03.463 --> 32:06.507
- And we don't even know who you are.
- Any last words?

32:15.850 --> 32:17.268
I propose

32:18.561 --> 32:20.897
we settle this like the warriors of Elbaph

32:21.856 --> 32:22.815
with a duel.

32:29.697 --> 32:33.825
Sorry, it's just, um… you versus us.

32:33.826 --> 32:35.786
I don't think that'll be a fair fight.

32:35.787 --> 32:36.996
Which is why I love it.

32:37.497 --> 32:38.498
Okay.

32:39.123 --> 32:41.960
- Which one of us do you want to duel?
- Her.

32:44.045 --> 32:45.380
She took Nami.

32:46.255 --> 32:47.589
And I want a rematch.

32:47.590 --> 32:51.135
Fine by me, darling.
I've been waiting to kill someone all day.

32:53.221 --> 32:57.433
In Elbaph, traditionally, a duel begins
with a gesture of mutual respect.

32:58.226 --> 33:01.104
Like a bow or a handshake.

33:01.980 --> 33:03.522
I'd rather begin

33:03.523 --> 33:05.316
like this!

33:10.989 --> 33:12.156
Whoa!

33:22.750 --> 33:24.335
You're Miss Valentine, right?

33:25.253 --> 33:28.881
You come up with that code name yourself?
'Cause you don't seem very sweet.

33:31.426 --> 33:32.552
I am

33:33.177 --> 33:35.304
incredibly sweet!

33:39.017 --> 33:41.101
Get out here and help me!

33:41.102 --> 33:43.854
Two against one?
Not exactly a duel, is it?

33:43.855 --> 33:46.231
Let's talk about your partner!
He got a raw deal.

33:46.232 --> 33:49.276
What's his devil fruit again?
Exploding boogers?

33:49.277 --> 33:50.153
Hey!

33:50.778 --> 33:51.946
That's just nasty.

34:01.164 --> 34:03.291
You never shut up, do you?

34:04.000 --> 34:06.794
Guess I'll have to make you.

34:07.462 --> 34:08.713
That was 20 kilo.

34:10.048 --> 34:11.548
Fifty kilo!

34:11.549 --> 34:13.384
I can barely feel it.

34:14.469 --> 34:17.722
One hundred kilo!

34:19.223 --> 34:21.142
Why are you smiling?

34:21.642 --> 34:23.185
You're about to die.

34:23.186 --> 34:24.896
An honorable death,

34:25.396 --> 34:27.356
saving my friends.

34:29.025 --> 34:30.901
Uh…

34:30.902 --> 34:31.903
Val?

35:06.687 --> 35:08.021
Thanks for saving us.

35:08.022 --> 35:09.648
Uh-huh.

35:09.649 --> 35:12.901
Let's make this fight a bit more fair.
I'll get him.

35:12.902 --> 35:13.778
We'll get her.

35:24.205 --> 35:28.876
We know all about you, Monkey D. Luffy.

35:30.920 --> 35:34.215
Baroque Works always researches
our targets.

35:35.925 --> 35:38.261
To learn their strengths.

35:40.680 --> 35:43.891
And especially their weaknesses.

35:44.475 --> 35:45.726
I've studied yours.

35:46.435 --> 35:48.311
You're a bruiser.

35:48.312 --> 35:50.606
You rush in blindly.

35:51.440 --> 35:54.235
Strike without thinking.

35:57.780 --> 35:59.615
I, on the other hand,

36:00.575 --> 36:02.952
always come prepared.

36:20.344 --> 36:21.595
Am I still alive?

36:21.596 --> 36:23.347
Happy Valentine's Day!

36:26.350 --> 36:28.811
- Get away from my friend.
- Our friend.

36:30.313 --> 36:34.025
Oh, please, Miss Wednesday.
You were never on my level.

36:38.112 --> 36:39.780
Roronoa Zoro,

36:40.281 --> 36:41.657
trapped like a rat.

36:43.242 --> 36:44.492
You love to see it.

36:44.493 --> 36:47.245
Bet you do.
It's the only way you stand a chance.

36:47.246 --> 36:49.164
You even know
how to fight without those swords?

36:49.165 --> 36:51.292
You know how to fight
without picking your nose?

36:55.504 --> 36:58.132
My breeze breath bullets
pack one hell of a punch.

37:02.553 --> 37:05.680
Gum Gum Stamp Gatling!

37:05.681 --> 37:09.644
Da! Da! Da! Da! Da! Da! Da! Da!
Da! Da! Da! Da! Da! Da! Da! Da!

37:24.450 --> 37:25.451
Night night.

37:31.540 --> 37:32.832
You missed.

37:32.833 --> 37:34.751
You're a real pain in my ass, you know?

37:34.752 --> 37:36.962
How about a pain in your mouth?

37:36.963 --> 37:38.297
Special Tabasco Star!

38:05.157 --> 38:06.367
Aah!

38:49.994 --> 38:51.162
Aah!

39:00.463 --> 39:01.589
Ha!

39:24.236 --> 39:27.156
Cute stick. Seems a bit fragile!

39:28.991 --> 39:30.658
Oops.

39:30.659 --> 39:33.329
You wanted to die looking cool.
Now you're going out like a chump!

39:44.382 --> 39:45.633
This is for Igaram.

39:50.137 --> 39:51.222
Zoro!

39:51.764 --> 39:53.557
Surekill Flame Star.

39:55.851 --> 39:56.769
Aah!

40:15.704 --> 40:16.705
Dorry?

40:20.459 --> 40:22.294
How do you like my sculpture?

40:23.754 --> 40:26.841
Gum Gum Pistol!

40:30.803 --> 40:32.096
Hmm.

40:32.596 --> 40:35.473
Aah! Aah!

40:35.474 --> 40:36.809
Candle Lock!

40:46.902 --> 40:48.695
You did that to Dorry.

40:48.696 --> 40:50.823
You don't fight with honor!

40:52.032 --> 40:54.118
But those giants did.

40:54.618 --> 40:57.203
That's what made them such easy targets.

40:57.204 --> 40:58.205
Aah!

41:00.958 --> 41:03.002
Like you.

41:05.921 --> 41:09.340
Trying to punch your way
through every problem.

41:09.341 --> 41:10.801
I'll never give up.

41:11.635 --> 41:15.180
Oh, I prefer to view it as
you'll never learn.

41:15.181 --> 41:16.098
Aah!

41:16.765 --> 41:17.932
Hmm.

41:17.933 --> 41:19.935
It appears our research was wrong.

41:22.354 --> 41:24.689
You're all too easy to take down.

41:24.690 --> 41:29.445
Almost as easy as those poor, dumb giants.

41:41.290 --> 41:44.210
Those giants were my friends.

41:48.589 --> 41:50.508
And you dishonored them.

41:54.512 --> 41:56.429
Candle Wall!

41:56.430 --> 41:59.266
Gum Gum Hammer!

42:24.458 --> 42:26.626
Luffy! You're okay.

42:26.627 --> 42:29.630
- We are too, somehow.
- Usopp saved the day.

42:32.049 --> 42:34.635
- Of course he did.
- What the hell happened here?

42:36.220 --> 42:37.470
Sanji!

42:37.471 --> 42:38.347
Hey.

42:38.931 --> 42:41.641
I really can't leave you lot alone, can I?

42:41.642 --> 42:42.892
Where have you been?

42:42.893 --> 42:44.727
Don't worry. I saved the day.

42:44.728 --> 42:47.313
I don't know if you heard,
but it was pretty cool.

42:47.314 --> 42:49.608
- Well, look what I found.
- Ooh.

42:50.192 --> 42:53.361
- An Eternal Pose?
- And it's set to Alabasta.

42:53.362 --> 42:54.779
Oh!

42:54.780 --> 42:56.990
Sanji!

42:56.991 --> 42:59.659
- You're amazing!
- I guess I saved the day too.

42:59.660 --> 43:02.704
This is great. We don't have to wait
for our Log Pose to reset.

43:02.705 --> 43:04.038
Uh! Mm-mm.

43:04.039 --> 43:05.332
Let's get the hell out of here.

43:06.875 --> 43:08.668
Please!

43:08.669 --> 43:10.713
Before something else tries to kill us.

43:13.591 --> 43:15.425
So we've had dinosaurs.

43:15.426 --> 43:18.137
- Assassins.
- Are we forgetting anything else?

43:20.806 --> 43:22.265
Ah, yeah.

43:22.266 --> 43:23.349
The giants.

43:23.350 --> 43:26.645
Dorry was trapped in the wax too,
so I set him free.

43:32.985 --> 43:35.904
Did you all know
there were giants on this island?

43:40.326 --> 43:43.953
Oh, my dearest friend.
I thank the gods you're alive.

43:43.954 --> 43:45.997
And I thank the gods you're alive.

43:45.998 --> 43:48.791
But stop hugging me so tightly,
or you'll open my wound.

43:48.792 --> 43:51.127
We're happy that you're both alive.

43:51.128 --> 43:53.171
We giants are a hearty lot.

43:53.172 --> 43:56.466
After you freed me from that wax,
I felt good as new.

43:56.467 --> 44:02.348
Oh, yes. And one taste of his stew
could bring anyone back from the dead.

44:05.809 --> 44:07.685
What about your duel?

44:07.686 --> 44:09.062
You're not still…

44:09.063 --> 44:11.148
After 100 years with no victor,

44:12.316 --> 44:15.027
we think the gods
have made their judgment plain.

44:18.030 --> 44:18.864
I owe you

44:19.907 --> 44:21.407
for what you said back there.

44:21.408 --> 44:24.160
No, I owe you.

44:24.161 --> 44:26.914
Now we have a new tale to tell.

44:27.498 --> 44:31.709
The legend of brave warrior Usopp.

44:31.710 --> 44:32.878
Yeah!

44:34.380 --> 44:36.005
And I have a new dream.

44:36.006 --> 44:38.132
I'm gonna visit Elbaph one day.

44:38.133 --> 44:40.968
Oh, you'll fit right in.

44:40.969 --> 44:45.182
Well, maybe you'll stand out a little.

44:47.685 --> 44:48.686
Princess,

44:49.520 --> 44:51.396
I pray your country is safe.

44:51.397 --> 44:52.647
Thank you, Dorry.

44:52.648 --> 44:54.149
When you sail away,

44:54.775 --> 45:00.781
trust in us, and sail straight ahead
no matter what happens.

45:01.365 --> 45:03.116
What? No matter what happens?

45:03.117 --> 45:07.788
- What do you mean, no matter what happens?
- See ya! Try not to die anymore!

45:11.250 --> 45:12.166
Hmm.

45:12.167 --> 45:16.546
<i>Hail to the one
Follow the great warrior's way</i>

45:16.547 --> 45:19.048
<i>Go on, pray to the sun
Pray to the sun</i>

45:19.049 --> 45:21.884
<i>Pray, oh, pray, oh</i>

45:21.885 --> 45:25.555
Luffy? I've diverted you
from your journey long enough.

45:25.556 --> 45:28.142
The next ship we pass,
I'll ask them for passage.

45:28.642 --> 45:30.519
I'll use the Eternal Pose to get home.

45:31.186 --> 45:32.687
That's too bad.

45:32.688 --> 45:35.399
I already asked Nami
to set course to Alabasta.

45:40.487 --> 45:42.656
I… I… I can't ask you to take me.

45:44.616 --> 45:46.076
You didn't have to.

45:48.370 --> 45:49.830
Like I said…

45:52.166 --> 45:53.709
when you see it, you see it.

45:57.546 --> 45:59.422
Our new friends have set sail.

45:59.423 --> 46:03.384
They won't get very far
with that monster in the water.

46:03.385 --> 46:05.721
At least, not without our help.

46:07.473 --> 46:11.100
I've fought with my Bruiser axe
for over a hundred years.

46:11.101 --> 46:12.978
And I, my Terry sword.

46:14.021 --> 46:17.232
But if our dueling days are over,

46:17.733 --> 46:20.194
I can't think of a better way
to say goodbye.

46:21.695 --> 46:25.907
Oh! Guys! There's something
swimming right for us!

46:25.908 --> 46:27.074
Is it another dinosaur?

46:27.075 --> 46:28.118
Is it a Sea King?

46:32.414 --> 46:35.209
It's a giant goldfish!

46:38.670 --> 46:40.087
Port the helm!

46:40.088 --> 46:41.214
No!

46:41.215 --> 46:42.549
We sail straight ahead.

46:43.050 --> 46:44.383
Just like Brogy said.

46:44.384 --> 46:47.094
Hakoku…

46:47.095 --> 46:50.098
Sovereignty!

46:57.022 --> 46:58.357
- Whoa!
- Whoa.

47:04.905 --> 47:06.531
Did you see that?

47:06.532 --> 47:07.532
Whoo!

47:07.533 --> 47:10.702
That was amazing!

47:13.580 --> 47:16.416
May good fortune be with you!

47:19.795 --> 47:21.546
Excellent shot, my friend.

47:21.547 --> 47:24.924
Equally excellent to yours.

47:24.925 --> 47:28.845
You know, I suddenly recall
what started our duel in the first place.

47:28.846 --> 47:30.304
That's right.

47:30.305 --> 47:32.598
We had each taken down
an enormous Sea King.

47:32.599 --> 47:34.934
And we were asked which one was bigger.

47:34.935 --> 47:36.561
Mine was, of course.

47:36.562 --> 47:37.687
Hogwash!

47:37.688 --> 47:40.106
The beast I felled was clearly bigger!

47:40.107 --> 47:41.858
Do you question my honor?

47:41.859 --> 47:44.235
Your honor? I question your sanity!

47:44.236 --> 47:47.071
Then perhaps we should settle
this once and for all.

47:47.072 --> 47:49.157
With a duel!

47:50.492 --> 47:51.492
Aah!

47:51.493 --> 47:53.703
Damn it.
I could've made sushi out of that.

47:53.704 --> 47:55.538
- No.
- I take on fish every day.

47:55.539 --> 47:59.042
- Not ones that size, you don't.
- Don't you worry about me and size.

48:00.669 --> 48:01.795
Idiots.

48:12.306 --> 48:13.890
<i>See what you've done?</i>

48:13.891 --> 48:15.224
We lost the fight,

48:15.225 --> 48:19.605
your partner lost her mind,
and our targets got away… again!

48:20.147 --> 48:22.983
I told you we should've killed them
when we had the chance.

48:29.239 --> 48:30.657
He's going to want answers.

48:34.745 --> 48:36.330
I'm going to tell him the truth.

48:36.914 --> 48:38.373
This was all your fault.

48:43.211 --> 48:46.548
You won't be telling him anything.

48:56.725 --> 49:00.186
- Best dinosaur I've ever tasted!
- Have you tasted dinosaur before?

49:00.187 --> 49:02.730
No. But I don't think
it can taste better than this.

49:02.731 --> 49:04.482
The challenge was finding
a pan big enough.

49:04.483 --> 49:06.150
I think we earned a good meal.

49:06.151 --> 49:07.234
That's right!

49:07.235 --> 49:08.695
Hmm. Hmm?

49:10.197 --> 49:11.281
All right, everyone.

49:12.866 --> 49:13.909
Hmm.

49:14.618 --> 49:15.953
To the hero of Little Garden.

49:16.870 --> 49:17.871
Huh?

49:19.289 --> 49:20.247
To Usopp.

49:20.248 --> 49:22.626
To Usopp!

49:23.669 --> 49:25.462
Aren't you gonna tell a story?

49:26.421 --> 49:27.464
I can't.

49:31.385 --> 49:34.971
Okay, so there I was.
Me alone, surrounded by six assassins.

49:34.972 --> 49:36.973
- Uh… six?
- Maybe there was eight.

49:36.974 --> 49:38.934
They were moving fast.
You saw it. Right, Vivi?

49:39.726 --> 49:42.061
Uh… it was too hard to count.

49:42.062 --> 49:45.356
You know, Vivi, I did defeat
two Baroque Works agents myself.

49:45.357 --> 49:46.483
Which two?

49:46.984 --> 49:48.484
Miss Friday and Mr. 13.

49:48.485 --> 49:50.444
Wow. What were they like?

49:50.445 --> 49:51.863
I mean, they were, uh…

